comments: Ingram (NOP) initiates contact with Jackson Jr. (MEM) in the post and impedes him.

Williams Jr. (MEM) makes slight contact to Valanciunas's (NOP) head as he attempts to slip the screen.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Jones (NOP) is moving alongside Morant's (MEM) path and the body contact that occurs as they come together at the end of the drive is marginal.
Jones (NOP) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Tillman's (MEM) path and the contact that occurs during the pick is incidental.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) retreats and absorbs the body contact from Williamson (NOP) and when he lowers his arm, marginal contact occurs.
Bane (MEM) contests the layup attempt and the contact that occurs with Valanciunas's (NOP) arm after the release is marginal.
Jones (NOP) collapses his forearm as he absorbs the contact to Morant's (MEM) body during the driving shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Jones's (NOP) driving shot attempt.
Valanciunas (NOP) and Tillman (MEM) briefly engage and disengage with one another as Tillman attempts to establish a screening position.
Williamson (NOP) deflects the loose ball as both he and Williams Jr. (MEM) come together during the rebound.
Jones (NOP) establishes himself in Williams Jr.'s (MEM) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the pick.
Morant (MEM) grazes Ingram's (NOP) arm as he attempts to pass and the contact that occurs is marginal.
Morant (MEM) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two steps as he spins.
Jones (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position as incidental lower body contact occurs after the release of Morant's (MEM) driving shot attempt.
